The new developments in Perl syntax mostly solve this by having an explicit separator for invocant specification:<p><pre><code>    method foo ($bar, $baz) { ... }
</code></pre>
has $self, $bar and $baz, while<p><pre><code>    method foo ($class: $bar, $baz) { ... }
</code></pre>
has $class, $bar and $baz.
